fields.medical_officer_remarks: As per documents, 3 months/ Female patient was admitted from 20-11-2024 to 27-11-2024 under Dr. Chandrakant for the C/O-pain while urination since 7-8 days with h/o-fever 10-12 days before. Diagnosed as UTI-urine culture +ve ( Klebsiella SPP) and was treated conservatively. As per TD-patient admitted with C/O- pain while micturition (mostly at midnight) since 7-8 days with fever. Etiology is bacteria and other microbes enter urinary tract and cause UTI. Need of admission is due to UTI. Hospital is 45 bedded with 4 RMO, 16 doctors, 15 nursing staff. Admitted in Semi special which costing Rs.4000/- day, paid Rs. 29100/- against final hospital bill by online transactions. Hospital is 5 bedded. Treating doctor and pathologist registration details, verified on NMC site. As per Google review, hospital works 24/7 (4.2/5 rating). The distance between hospital and insured’s residence is approx. 6.7 km. Investigation done in SS Clinical lab but reports are signed and verified by DMLT person i.e. Mr. Kamalkar Ahirrao. No MD pathologist attached. Microbiology test report done in Aarmaan micro lab- after scanning QR code –report findings matched with submitted report. Some done in Rajole path lab, pathologist is Dr. Mahendra Rajole- registration details verified on NMC site.  Only ICP’s seems single stretched. No any other discrepancies found. Based on findings, said claim seems genuine hence recommended for payable.

fields.hospital_name: Sri Jayendra Saraswathi Ayurveda College & Hospital

fields.medical_officer_remarks: claim is closed as a payable

As per given documents, 36 yrs. male patient was admitted in Shree Parth Multispeciality hospital which located at 2R97+H92, Hirawadi Rd, Hirawadi, Nashik, Maharashtra 422207, From 14-11-2024  9.30 pm to 19-11-2024 5.20 pm, for the C/O- high grade fever with chills, severe headache, severe bodyache, breathlessness, cough with expectoration, severe low back pain. O/E- BP-110/62, P-128, T-102.3, SPO2-95%. Diagnosed as LRTI with viral hemorrhagic fever dengue and was treated conservatively. As per TD- Admitted in ICU and special room. Diagnosed as LRTI, etiology is viral. Hospital is 15 bedded with 3 RMO and 2 doctors. Based on collected documents, below discrepancies noted. 
•	 No any specific details available on goggle regarding said hospital i.e. working hours, hospital photos, doctors availability, contact details etc.
•	The treating doctor, Dr. Kapil Patil, whose registration number (2023/10/7634) does not appear in the National Medical Commission (NMC) database, raises doubts about the doctor's credentials and authenticity.
•	The provided medicine bills lack GST numbers, which raises concerns about their legitimacy. 
•	According to a medical store letter dated 27-12-2024, the store is new and awaiting GST registration (but denied for any application /documentary evidences). Currently purchasing all on individual pan card. 
•	All medicine bills are in serial numbers.
•	Medicine charges are high, with examples of inflated costs for certain medications, casting suspicion on the accuracy and fairness of the pricing. for eg. Inj MPS 125 MG, magnex forte 1.5 gm injection etc.  
•	Pathologist Dr. D. P. Rajput (MBBS-071082) registration details verified on NMC site but Parth pathology laboratory –Panchvati, details not found on goggle. During visit we found, pathology is in hospital only, but only one cell counter machine found, no X-Ray and other machines found. No one is available in the pathology during our 2-3 visits.  
•	 The Given barcode on all lab reports are unable to scan, as per pathology letter- pathology is working since 6 months, they have barcode error since lab is working but not yet resolved the issues.  
•	Hospital is having in-house medical store and pharmacy, so it’s easy for them to manipulate the bill and reports. 
•	Pathology bills are not in proper sequence, and on every bill it’s mentioned paid amount is zero and due amount is actual pathology bill.  
Date 	pathology Bill No  	Amount  
14-11-24	202411410	4850
15-11-24	202412151	4950
16-11-24	202411614	1050
17-11-24	202411175	1050
18-11-24	202411187	1050
19-11-24	202411196	1050
•	As patient is admitted for viral hemorrhagic fever and prolonged stay is due to persistent fever but he was afebrile since 2nd day of admission. 
•	 TPR/BP/ Medicine chart are fully single stretched. 
•	All bill amount paid by cash. 
•	The hospital denied providing a tariff card, stating it was not kept, which hinders an accurate comparison of charges with standard rates.
•	As per final bill, consulting charges, room charges are seems on higher side according to hospital status (it’s only 15 bedded). 
•	During our 2-3 visit we found that, no one is available in the pathology, medical store and all details given to us was provided by the Hospital TPA/ Receptionist Mr.  
•	During our 1st visit we found that, no one was available in the hospital till 11.30 am-12.00 pm except one receptionist. After our visit one TPA staff and one pathology staff came and provide the available details.  
•	Night vicinity done, hospital was open.  
•	Treating doctor was not available during our visits, hence we asked them to provide his contact number and alternate hospital/clinic address to meet them, firstly hospital staff told doctor will come in the afternoon I,e. after 3.00 pm hence out field executive waited there till 4.00 pm but no one come. In last the concern person told that treating doctor went outstation for 2 days in emergency.  Which clearly indicates the suspiciousness.  
•	Treating doctor also denied to meet us.  
•	Treating doctor and key staff were repeatedly unavailable during visits.
•	Unclear operational status of the pathology and medical store.
•	Excessive use of antibiotics like inj augmentin, inj magnex forte, inj oflox are administed in BD, which is unnecessary. 
•	•Patient diagnosed as viral hemorrhagic fever with reddish patched but no SDP administered, as this may had led to internal bleeding and other diseases.
•	Inj solumedrol which is a steroid is advised by the doctor (ICP- pg no. 4), which is unnecessary, but is not added in the medication chart. 
•	According to the provided lab reports, patient is widal positive but not mentioned anywhere in the ICPs by TD doctor.
•	As per LFT report, bilirubin levels are high with the said symptoms, but no USG done to rule out any underlying causes.
•	D-Dimer, S. creatinine level are raised but no urine I/O charting maintained or supporting medication given. 
•	High valued medications are given to inflate the bill amount.
•	The repeated unavailability of key medical staff, the lack of transparency in billing and medical records, inflated charges, and failure to provide proper documentation lead to the conclusion that there may be fraudulent activity or manipulation in the billing and medical practices of the hospital.

The claim exhibits multiple inconsistencies, including unverified medical staff credentials, inflated billing, lack of transparency, and indications of fraudulent activities. Based on the findings, the claim is deemed manipulative and is recommended for rejection.
